Please don't feed 
the troll.</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#330000>(6/12/04 3:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19490.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> They dont know what they are going to do</span><hr size=1> They still have really no idea what they are going to do with charm.<br>
<br>
In fact right now they would really like to eliminate the enchanter class entirely (and the bard class) as both make their lives living hell from a design point of view.  Enchanter abilities 100% scale with the power of the NPCs and as such enchanters currently have two modes:<br>
<br>
Overpowered and Gimped.<br>
<br>
Overpowered if we can mez/charm/AE_stun because those powers allow us to remove mobs from combat and in some cases use their insane DPS to kill things making us the highest DPS class in the game by an order of magnitude.<br>
<br>
Gimped if we cant mez/charm/AE_stun because we've had essentially every other ability taken away from us because of the perceived power of the above.<br>
<br>
Look at the OOW spell list : no more strength buffs, no more cripple (always before shared with shaman), no MR buff, no Tash, no AC buff, no new slow, we don't even get a root(always shared the best with wizards)! We have a number of spell-lines that have been dead since Kunark all because we're perceived as grossly overpowered when our abilities work...and then because content never takes them into account they simply turn them off at the content level.<br>
<br>
The reason is that they are, right now, 100% banking on the 'new charm' being the lifeblood of the enchanter class.  That is the entire strategy and its dependent on the 'new charm' being balanced which is somebody elses problem.<br>
<br>
The only non-core (Haste, Clarity, token crappy DPS nuke) spells they've given the enchanter class in OOW are 100% about charm.  New charms (2 of them) new self-rune, new-target rune, new non-reagent rune, AE stun.  There is no Morell or Tash which is just silly as Morell is the only way we can use charm currently so I expect it will be created.  If it isnt created then there will be no using charm...period, but I digress.<br>
<br>
The 'new charm' hinges on the ability to scale back the DPS and abilities of a mob when charmed.  A bit of this made it into GoD but not all of it, hence why in early GoD mobs were charmable and did lots of DPS.  They don't know where to draw the line however.  Do they make the mob use no abilities at all?  Do they make the mob do a flat 25% of its normal DPS?  30? 50?  If so does the mob go back to 100% strnegth immediately when charm breaks?  If that is the case then we will be FORBIDDEN from using charm in most situations as the instant we die our pet becomes a huge liability.  Even in situations now, where the pet is a nice asset as well as a huge liability, its rare to allow them to be used on a raid because of the potential for disaster when charm does break.<br>
<br>
When faced directly with these questions the EQ Devs last weekend sighed and said &quot;we don't know, we're thinking about it, but we don't know&quot;<br>
<br>
In my opinion to make it viable you have to do two things.  One, make the damage of the pet high enough to make it very attractive to use, but low enough that enchanters arent the highest DPS class in the game by an order of magnitude.  Two, make the risk comparably lower by having a 3 tick &quot;dizzy&quot; effect activate whenever a mob breaks charm which keeps its charmed DPS and ability rate while recovering from just being charmed.  This would allow easier recharming/add-tanking/mezzing and would prevent a newly broken charm from ripping apart all your friends and neighbors for at leas 18 seconds after charm broke.  <br>
<br>
The problem then is bards (and yes Voice of the Vampire does indeed currently have a level 70 cap pretty sure thats an error) because with this 'new charm' concept they could either ALSO have a very nice pet instead of other very nice abilities, but more dangerous from a design standpoint they could chain charm a mob, with no intention of keeping it charmed, purely for the 'dizzy' debuff.  Charm a mob, invis instantly, charmed mob is now 'dizzy' for 18 seconds and easier to kill, recharm mob after 3 ticks, invis instantly  repeat.   <br>
<br>
The other difficulty is in encounter design.  Right now designers are accustomed to making lots of mobs flagged mez,charm, and stun immune.  Content would have to be designed with the 'new charm' in mind and that probably wouldnt happen.  Afterall there was a HUGE disconnect with GoD where tons and tons of mobs were not flagged mez_immune but were mezzable mobs higher than the current mez cap and were antipating the new level 67 mez spell that would work up to level 70.  Even many months after it was made clear that the level 68 for the 5th anniversary was NOT going to happen these mobs were still &gt; level 68 and thus non mezzable.  Some in Txevu still remain so to this day, a legacy of the failure of GoD to implement the planned 'birthday suprise' of the level cap increase.<br>
<br>
So to make 'new charm' work they need to make some hard decisions about how the ability needs to operate and then still have to craft content carefully around it and other CC abilities...something which they don't like having to deal with which is why its just easier to flag the whole damn thing immune and not bother. <br>
<br>
There is a heck of alot of effort involved for just one or two classes.  Its much easier to just tweak up or down the damage on a sword or a wizard nuke and hence why they really wish it would just go away. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lasialifeseeker>Lasia Lifeseeker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 138<br> <font color=#330000>(6/12/04 6:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19490.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: They dont know what they are going to do</span><hr size=1> Well Charm use to be the only CC a bard had..was nice dps and kinda fun.<br>
