<br>
You know ... Charm was one of the first strategies that was posted in the Bard boards, here and Rokken's that I can remember - I still have that print out and article! ... and in a way could be considered one of the very first &quot;exploits&quot; that led to the Bard being who the Bard is now ... it was merely expanded by accident to Swarm Kiting, when the aggro rules were changed and messed with and all of a sudden all the mobs attack the pet ... I don't remember this being as well defined then as it is now ... but then, not all the mobs moved as much, or as far, as they do now. Guk had one wonderer at the entry, and one at the T and those were easy.  To my knowledge, and I was just starting then, Froon and Choon were the first high profile victims of this, and eventually folks graduated to the Rathe Mountains and so on.<br>
<br>
I find it unfair, and sad, when someone says that this is powerfull and what not, and requests a removal. I can only surmise that you do not play a Bard at all, or have ever had the verve to be able to swarm kite (I can't with bad eye and glasses - too hard and I get dizzy), and appreciate the talent that it takes (if not the machine) which helped define so much in this game ... adjustments since then include the timer on the mob (used to be random up to 24 seconds or something like it, and tied to your Charisma and Wind Instrument skill), the use of mana to prevent someone from doing it all day long and nothing else but chant/swarm kite, the range was changed, the mob's attention span was changed, and other things including tougher targeting at one time and what not.  Many of these details became very important and was, in essence no different than the adjustments they made to Necromancers and Druids doing the 3 Sisters in Butcherblock, although they could not Charm Kite, but AE kited with a long range that has also been changed since, which Bards also learned to work with, eventually.<br>
<br>
Charm, was one of the very first tools that helped the Bard in the early days ... and for someone to speak out and trash it (NOW!) would mean they have no idea of the history of the Charm in this game with Bards, and how folks learned to do so many things that are taken for granted today ... if I may ... mind your manners young man! <p>Moshkiae Soulwriter, the non role playing Bard / Mo'riae Soulwriter - Cleric</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=moshkiae>Moshkiae</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/12/04 9:16 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khalm>khalm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#330000>(6/12/04 10:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19490.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: They dont know what they are going to do</span><hr size=1> charm cap needs to be high. in most zones that a 65+ bard will be grouping in there just isnt any low lvl mobs, so to make a charm that caps on lvl 60 mobs would be just as useful as our current charm that caps on lvl 57 mobs... useless.<br>
